{
  "info": {
    "name": "IDFC \u2014 SFDC user-management (org-targeted egress)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": "Tests the sfdc-user-management SYNC capability on the DIGITAL EDGE (POST /api/v1/sfdcUserManagement, :8081). svcName selects the operation; orgName selects WHICH SFDC org instance is called (org-targeted egress). Requests carry pm.test assertions, so `newman run` gates them.\n\nBRANCH-ONLY: this endpoint + the two SFDC org WireMocks live on branch claude/code-review-bug-design-u568d3, not main. Prereqs: (1) build+run the digital edge from that branch; (2) docker compose -f docker-compose.infra.yml up -d so mock-sfdc-org-a (:19112) and mock-sfdc-org-b (:19113) are live. Only the mock DATA is mocked \u2014 each org's response carries an `org` field so routing is provable.\n\nAuth = Authorization: Bearer {{syncToken}} (the same fail-closed sync-edge token as impsFT/callLmsUtilities; dev = dev-sync-token). Import into Postman or Insomnia."
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "edgeBase",
      "value": "http://localhost:8081"
    },
    {
      "key": "syncToken",
      "value": "dev-sync-token"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Reads \u2014 org routing proof",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Fetch user \u2014 ORG_A",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"routed to ORG_A (HTTP 200)\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().org).to.eql(\"ORG_A\");",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{syncToken}}"
              },
              {
                "key": "correlationId",
                "value": "sfdc-{{$guid}}"
              },
              {
                "key": "source",
                "value": "JMI"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"svcName\": \"SFDC_USER_FETCH\",\n  \"orgName\": \"ORG_A\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"Username\": \"asha.rao@orga.example.com\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{edgeBase}}/api/v1/sfdcUserManagement",
              "host": [
                "{{edgeBase}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "sfdcUserManagement"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Read (no idempotency key). Routes to mock-sfdc-org-a (:19112) -> response org=ORG_A."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Fetch user \u2014 ORG_B (same svcName, other org)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"routed to ORG_B (HTTP 200)\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().org).to.eql(\"ORG_B\");",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{syncToken}}"
              },
              {
                "key": "correlationId",
                "value": "sfdc-{{$guid}}"
              },
              {
                "key": "source",
                "value": "JMI"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"svcName\": \"SFDC_USER_FETCH\",\n  \"orgName\": \"ORG_B\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"Username\": \"vikram.rao@orgb.example.com\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{edgeBase}}/api/v1/sfdcUserManagement",
              "host": [
                "{{edgeBase}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "sfdcUserManagement"
              ]
            },
            "description": "SAME svcName, orgName=ORG_B -> routes to mock-sfdc-org-b (:19113) -> org=ORG_B. THIS is the org-routing proof: the org name, not the svcName, chose the target."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Writes \u2014 idempotency + business/technical",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create user \u2014 ORG_A (success)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"HTTP 200, success=true\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.eql(true);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{syncToken}}"
              },
              {
                "key": "correlationId",
                "value": "sfdc-{{$guid}}"
              },
              {
                "key": "source",
                "value": "JMI"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"svcName\": \"SFDC_USER_CREATE\",\n  \"orgName\": \"ORG_A\",\n  \"idempotencyKey\": \"idem-{{$guid}}\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"Username\": \"new.user@orga.example.com\",\n    \"LastName\": \"Rao\",\n    \"Email\": \"new.user@orga.example.com\",\n    \"ProfileId\": \"00eXX0000000001\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{edgeBase}}/api/v1/sfdcUserManagement",
              "host": [
                "{{edgeBase}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "sfdcUserManagement"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Write. Mandatory idempotencyKey (unique {{$guid}} here). 200 success:true + id + org=ORG_A."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create user \u2014 idempotency REPLAY (fixed key)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"HTTP 200, success=true\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.eql(true);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{syncToken}}"
              },
              {
                "key": "correlationId",
                "value": "sfdc-{{$guid}}"
              },
              {
                "key": "source",
                "value": "JMI"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"svcName\": \"SFDC_USER_CREATE\",\n  \"orgName\": \"ORG_A\",\n  \"idempotencyKey\": \"idem-fixed-001\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"Username\": \"replay.user@orga.example.com\",\n    \"LastName\": \"Rao\",\n    \"Email\": \"replay.user@orga.example.com\",\n    \"ProfileId\": \"00eXX0000000001\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{edgeBase}}/api/v1/sfdcUserManagement",
              "host": [
                "{{edgeBase}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "sfdcUserManagement"
              ]
            },
            "description": "SEND THIS TWICE. Both return the identical body; the capability calls SFDC only ONCE \u2014 the second is a cached replay keyed by idempotencyKey (idem-fixed-001). In the edge log you'll see one 'write done' then one 'idempotent replay'. (Reset by changing the key.)"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create user \u2014 DUPLICATE (business no, still 200)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"HTTP 200, success=false\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.eql(false);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{syncToken}}"
              },
              {
                "key": "correlationId",
                "value": "sfdc-{{$guid}}"
              },
              {
                "key": "source",
                "value": "JMI"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"svcName\": \"SFDC_USER_CREATE\",\n  \"orgName\": \"ORG_A\",\n  \"idempotencyKey\": \"idem-{{$guid}}\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"Username\": \"DUPE_USER\",\n    \"LastName\": \"Rao\",\n    \"Email\": \"DUPE_USER\",\n    \"ProfileId\": \"00eXX0000000001\"\n  }\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{edgeBase}}/api/v1/sfdcUserManagement",
              "host": [
                "{{edgeBase}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "sfdcUserManagement"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Username=DUPE_USER triggers the mock's success:false + DUPLICATE_USERNAME. This is a BUSINESS 'no' (HTTP 200, returned as a body, audited BUSINESS_FAILURE) \u2014 NOT a technical error."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update user \u2014 ORG_A",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"HTTP 200, success=true\", function () {",
